      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (relative hemolysis index, volume-averaged shear stress, exposure time) are directly linked to the clinical endpoint of hemolysis and the regulatory acceptance criterion.",
      "rationale": "The primary QoI is the relative hemolysis index (RH), which directly maps to the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1 vs. predicate). Secondary QoIs include volume-averaged shear stress and scalar exposure time used in the power-law hemolysis model. All QoIs are mechanistically linked to erythrocyte damage and are established in the blood pump literature."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
