      "rationale": "Validation activities used the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump — the identical geometry as the COU device. Bovine blood at physiological hematocrit was used, consistent with accepted surrogate for human blood in hemolysis testing. Operating range (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM) encompasses the COU operating envelope. Validation relevance is high for MRL 2."
    },
    {
