      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Turbulence model selection (SST k-omega) justified against published blood pump validation studies; hemolysis power-law model parameters sourced from peer-reviewed calibration data.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published comparative studies for centrifugal blood pumps demonstrating superior wall shear stress prediction vs. standard k-epsilon. Giersiepen power-law hemolysis model with Heuser-Opitz constants adopted from peer-reviewed calibration. Model form uncertainty acknowledged and bounded by the 6.3% mean validation error."
    },
